pesticide.PPE: Coveralls; chemical-resistant gloves Category A (butyl rubber, natural rubber, neoprene rubber, nitrile rubber); shoes and socks; protective eyewear; chemical-resistant headgear for overhead exposure

Safety_Information.general_Info: KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_Inhaled: Move person to fresh air. If person is not breathing, call 911 or an ambulance, center or doctor for further treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
